    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS FUTURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"This event represents Scrooge’s experience of seeing the consequences of his actions in the future, prompted by the Ghost of Christmas Future."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WORKHOUSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Workhouses are institutions mentioned by the Spirit as a reflection of societal neglect and poverty."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOB CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk and a recipient of Scrooge's generosity after his transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk who benefits from Scrooge's newfound kindness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk who faces financial struggles; he is part of a large family and becomes a beneficiary of Scrooge's generosity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, known for his kindness and family, who appears in visions with his sister Fan."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, portrayed as a kind-hearted man struggling to make ends meet with his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's employee who works under poor conditions but remains kind-hearted. He is married and has a family that Scrooge later shows compassion towards."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a clerk working for Scrooge, living in poverty with his family, but maintains a cheerful demeanor despite his circumstances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a hardworking man with a large family, described as having 'no more than half-a-crown a week' and living in a small house. He is portrayed as a loving father who dotes on his son Tiny Tim."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is mentioned as the father of the household, with his wife and children experiencing emotional reactions to the news of his potential death."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is mentioned indirectly as Scrooge's clerk; he is a key character in 'A Christmas Carol' but appears later in the story."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is not explicitly mentioned in the provided text but is a significant character in 'A Christmas Carol,' known for his kindness despite his difficult life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the underpaid clerk of Scroodge, living in Camden Town and participating in festive activities on Christmas Eve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob is a kind-hearted clerk in Scrooge's office, supportive of his family and hopeful for change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4</data>
    </node>
