    <node id="&quot;TINY TIM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's deceased son, whose passing deeply impacts the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son who represents innocence; his condition and survival are significant in the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son who uses a crutch and has a hopeful outlook on life. His condition adds depth to the family dynamics."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, representing innocence and the vulnerable who benefit from Scrooge's transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, who is bedridden and represents the innocent victims of Scrooge's miserliness. His death in the future serves as a catalyst for Scrooge's transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob and Mrs. Cratchit's son, who is described as cripple and is cherished by the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob and Mrs. Cratchit's son, who is described as crippled and cherished by the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob and Mrs. Cratchit's youngest son, who is described as having a 'withered little hand' and being the focus of their affection. He is also mentioned to be at risk of dying if certain conditions remain unchanged."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Fred's son, representing innocence and joy at the gathering."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Scrooge's employee's son, symbolizing innocence and the impact of Scrooge's change."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a character whose condition is referenced in the text, highlighting the impact of the man's death on the family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a young, kind-hearted boy who dies due to his family's poverty and serves as a catalyst for Scrooge's transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4</data>
